    "notes": [
      {
        "componentKey": "n1",
        "kind": "pitfall",
        "text": "The 20–40 min window is huge because pan depth varies — in 2 thin layers a single layer can be done in 18–22 min while a deep 2-layer pan takes 35+. Start checking at 18 min and go by toothpick, not time.",
        "stepKey": "c2"
      },
      {
        "componentKey": "n2",
        "kind": "technique",
        "text": "This batter is built on pumpkin + applesauce with no oil or flour — it's very moist going in. Let layers cool completely (not just 10 min in-pan) before icing or the yogurt icing melts into the cake.",
        "stepKey": "c2"
      },
      {
        "componentKey": "n3",
        "kind": "technique",
        "text": "Soften the Laughing Cow wedges to room temp before mixing — cold wedges leave lumps in the icing that don't smooth out. Mix icing just before assembly; it thickens in the fridge if made too far ahead.",
        "stepKey": "iv1"
      },
      {
        "componentKey": "n4",
        "kind": "pitfall",
        "text": "The chocolate icing has only 1 tbsp cocoa versus the vanilla icing's none — both icings are protein-heavy (1 scoop each) and will firm up fast. Spread immediately after mixing; don't let them sit before applying.",
        "stepKey": "ic1"
      },
      {
        "componentKey": "n5",
        "kind": "technique",
        "text": "The 30-min fridge rest before slicing is essential — the Laughing Cow + yogurt icings need to set cold or they ooze out when cut. Cut with a sharp knife wiped clean between slices for clean tuxedo stripes.",
        "stepKey": "a1"
      }
    ]
  }
